Thailand Liveability Index — License Overview

This repository contains content under multiple licenses. Each layer is
tracked in a dedicated file. The default GitHub license-detector reads
this file; the substantive grants live in the linked files.

  CODE
    File:    LICENSE-CODE
    License: MIT
    Scope:   All source code in this repository — Astro components,
             TypeScript modules, Python scripts, GitHub Actions workflows,
             CSS, JSON-Schema files, and similar.
    Effect:  Free for any use, including commercial. No commercial
             license required for the code.

  METHODOLOGY AND DATA OUTPUTS (NON-COMMERCIAL)
    File:    LICENSE-DATA
    License: Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International
             (CC BY-NC 4.0)
    Scope:   Methodology document, indicator definitions, scoring
             algorithm documentation, score outputs (scores.json,
             scores.sample.json, indicator-meta.json, and any future
             score / methodology output emitted into src/data/).
    Effect:  Free for academic, journalistic, personal, civic,
             educational, and Thai-government use, with attribution.
             Commercial use requires a separate commercial license.

  METHODOLOGY AND DATA OUTPUTS (COMMERCIAL)
    File:    LICENSE-COMMERCIAL.md
    License: Separate commercial license required (placeholder; pricing
             deferred until commercial activation per the placeholder)
    Scope:   Same as LICENSE-DATA but for commercial use.
    Effect:  Email licensing@thailandliveabilityindex.com to begin a
             commercial-licensing conversation.

  TRADEMARKS
    File:    TRADEMARK.md
    Scope:   The names "Thailand Liveability Index" and "TLI", and any
             associated visual marks.
    Effect:  Trademark protection is layered on top of the open-source
             and Creative Commons licenses. The licenses cover the
             work; the trademark protects the identity. See TRADEMARK.md
             for what's open, what's protected, and what counts as
             acceptable use.

This repository is dual-licensed (MIT for code, CC BY-NC 4.0 for data
outputs) plus a separate commercial-license track and a trademark layer.
GitHub's default license detector will display "Other" or this LICENSE
file's contents in the sidebar; the binding grants live in
LICENSE-CODE, LICENSE-DATA, LICENSE-COMMERCIAL.md, and TRADEMARK.md.
